LEGO Exercise Learnings

1.

Accurate estimations of how many "points" a task is worth is very hard, constant reflections and updates is necessary.

2.

Defined roles where everyone knows what their task is and how to do it really speeds up the process.

3.

Stick to the (scrum-)plan, especially during the stressful parts of the project where you may be tempted to cut a few corners to speed things up.
In the long run it will only result in mistakes and confusion which builds more stress and tension in the team.
